				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEPs 17 and 19: HTTP Seeding.</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Yes, there are not any server side scripts or changes needed at all for BEP 19.&nbsp; <br /><br />As GetRight does it, any server would work, even if it doesn't support the byte-ranges.&nbsp; (For that case, a client can still start at 0 and get the first portions of the file from the server.)<br /><br />Plus the same methods work with any FTP servers as well--something that isn't possible in BEP 17.&nbsp; <br /><br /><br />I'm of course 100% biased, but I prefer the GetRight way <img src="img/smilies/smile.png" width="15" height="15" alt="smile" /><br /><br />Michael Burford<br />GetRight Author.</p>
				</div>
