				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEPs 17 and 19: HTTP Seeding.</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<blockquote><div class="incqbox"><p>Can anyone present benefits of the tornado spec over the getright one?</p></div></blockquote><p>It's somewhat simpler for the client to implement, and you can really threat the webseed as just another peer, which makes it easier to fit in from an architectural point of view. (Certainly for my client, KTorrent)<br /><br />The GetRight spec doesn't really have that, seeing that working one piece at a time is not really encouraged (though it could be done), you are more expected to download big blocks of data.<br /><br />Either way, I think the GetRight spec is probably the best way to go, seeing that it does not require server modifications.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
