				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEPs 17 and 19: HTTP Seeding.</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>i'm not quite sure, but wouldn't pipelining reduce the amount of tcp connections to the server? And logging is more or less an external issue not related to network performance that could be solved by disabling logging for each single request.<br /><br />But yes, making larger requests is certainly preferable, but can't be done all the time, e.g. when you already are at &gt; 50% then you'll have randomly distributed pieces and most gaps will be only 1-2 piece sizes large (although that's already more than 16KiB)</p>
				</div>
