<div id="p371" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#16&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=371#p371">2008-08-20 16:13:44</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=30435">bram</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Administrator</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Discussion of BEPs 17 and 19: HTTP Seeding.</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>To not pipeline HTTP requests is bad behavior.<br /><br />The biggest issues with web seeding have to do with behavior. There currently is no way to specify whether the client should optimize for dowload rate, offload, or some combination of both, and I bet that client implementations vary widely.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
